ed, 06 May 2026 15:32:07 GMT</pubDate><title>Why the Strait of Hormuz will take a long time to reboot</title><updateDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 06:50:33 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 07 May 2026 16:29:14 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The cruise ship at the center of the hantavirus outbreak is heading toward the Canary Islands in Spain. Contact tracing is underway in multiple countries including the United States after passengers left the ship before the first reported case. NBC News&#39; Matt Bodner reports on the latest details from the outbreak.</description><expires>2056-05-07T16:26:17.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">now_daily_a_virus_latest_260507</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/now/video/contact-tracing-underway-after-passengers-left-ship-before-first-reported-hantavirus-case-262921797779</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/now_daily_a_virus_latest_260507/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>Contact tracing underway after passengers left ship before first reported hantavirus case</media:title><media:player url="https://www.nbcnews.com/now/video/contact-tracing-underway-after-passengers-left-ship-before-first-reported-hantavirus-case-262921797779"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778171166154_now_daily_a_virus_latest_260507_S3_1920x1080-38jy4y.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">The cruise ship at the center of the hantavirus outbreak is heading toward the Canary Islands in Spain. Contact tracing is underway in multiple countries including the United States after passengers left the ship before the first reported case. NBC News&#39; Matt Bodner reports on the latest details from the outbreak.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778171166154_now_daily_a_virus_latest_260507.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778171166154_now_daily_a_virus_latest_260507.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778171166154_now_daily_a_virus_latest_260507_S3_1920x1080-38jy4y.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 16:26:14 GMT</pubDate><title>Contact tracing underway after passengers left ship before first reported hantavirus case</title><updateDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 16:29:14 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Suzanne Gamboa</dc:creator><dc:creator>Mike Hixenbaugh</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 07 May 2026 18:34:20 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Daniel Savala, who preached for decades in an Assemblies of God-run college ministry, was sentenced to 30 years in prison without the possibility of parole.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/daniel-savala-christian-missionary-pleads-guilty-abusing-boys-rcna343859</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/daniel-savala-christian-missionary-pleads-guilty-abusing-boys-rcna343859</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-07/250729-daniel-savala-group-cs-7e5e14.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1158" width="1606"><media:credit>Courtesy Olivia Wolf</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Savala poses with Eli Stewart and other young followers in Alaska in 2002.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Savala poses with Eli Stewart and other young followers in Alaska in 2002.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-savala-sentencing-joseph-cleveland-mn-1346-7b99d9.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1200" width="1800"><media:credit>Ilana Panich-Linsman for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Joseph Cleveland stands outside the courthouse before delivering his victim impact statement.</media:text><media:description type="plain">&#34;You thought yourself invincible,&#34; Joseph Cleveland told Daniel Savala while giving an impact statement in court Thursday.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-07/250722-joseph-cleveland-houston-house-mn-1300-7b81ba.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1363" width="2743"><media:credit>Courtesy Joseph Cleveland; Google Maps</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Joseph Cleveland as a young man; Daniel Savala&#39;s house in 2018.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Joseph Cleveland as a teen; Daniel Savala&#39;s house in 2018.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-savala-sentencing-ron-Bloomingkemper-mn-1346-0ddb4b.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1800" width="1440"><media:credit>Ilana Panich-Linsman for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Ron Bloomingkemper</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ron Bloomingkemper Jr., a former Chi Alpha member who for years raised alarm about Savala&#39;s actions, attended his plea hearing.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-savala-sentencing-joseph-cleveland-mn-1345-a2d6e5.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1200" width="1800"><media:credit>Ilana Panich-Linsman for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">From left, Krys Scroggins, Joseph Cleveland, Danny Clark, and far right, Ron Bloomingkemper, listen as Daniel Savala is sentenced.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Former Chi Alpha members, including Joseph Cleveland and Ron Bloomingkemper, listen as Daniel Savala is sentenced. </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-savala-sentencing-joseph-cleveland-mn-1350-357541.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1025" width="1370"><media:credit>Ilana Panich-Linsman for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Joseph Cleveland is embraced after the hearing where he gave an impact statement.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Joseph Cleveland hugs a victim support specialist from the prosecutor&#39;s office after Savala&#39;s guilty plea.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-07/250729-daniel-savala-group-cs-7e5e14.jpg" height="1158" width="1606"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 18:34:20 GMT</pubDate><title>Christian missionary hailed as ‘holiest man alive’ pleads guilty to abusing boys in Texas</title><updateDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 19:57:00 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Rebecca Keegan</dc:creator><dc:creator>Adam Reiss</dc:creator><dc:creator>Chloe Melas</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Saba Hamedy</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Daniel Arkin</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 07 May 2026 19:02:46 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>A federal judge on Thursday signed off on the settlement between Blake Lively and Justin Baldoni in their long-running legal dispute.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/pop-culture-news/blake-lively-justin-baldoni-legal-dispute-damages-countersuit-rcna344090</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/pop-culture-news/blake-lively-justin-baldoni-legal-dispute-damages-countersuit-rcna344090</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260505-blake-lively-justin-baldoni-mn-1030-12f067.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="800" width="1200"><media:credit>Getty Images</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Blake Lively; Justin Baldoni.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Blake Lively and Justin Baldoni.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260505-blake-lively-justin-baldoni-mn-1030-12f067.jpg" height="800" width="1200"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 19:02:46 GMT</pubDate><title>Blake Lively and Justin Baldoni’s legal spat may not be not fully resolved </title><updateDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 19:02:46 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Jon Schuppe</dc:creator><dc:creator>Mackenzie Mays, Bloomberg Law</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 07 May 2026 13:00:42 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The proposed legislation follows an investigation by Bloomberg Law and NBC News that found mistreatment of pregnant women in local jails. </description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/federal-bill-aims-protect-pregnant-women-prisons-jails-rcna342884</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/federal-bill-aims-protect-pregnant-women-prisons-jails-rcna342884</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260506-Sydney-Kamlager-Dove-vl-343p-cc75b4.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1503" width="2000"><media:credit>Heather Diehl</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Sydney Kamlager-Dove</media:text><media:description type="plain">Rep. Sydney Kamlager-Dove, D-Calif., during a House Judiciary Committee hearing in the Rayburn House Office Building on March 4, 2026.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-11/251113-kelsey-love-carousel-3-ew-440p-82eeb7.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Annie Flanagan for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Kelsey Love, also featured in the investigation, gave birth alone in jail after pleading for help. Her son survived.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Kelsey Love, also featured in the investigation, gave birth alone in jail after pleading for help. Her son survived.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-11/251113-chasity-congious-ew-440p-4a87e1.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="2500" width="2000"><media:credit>Annie Flanagan for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Bloomberg Law and NBC News&#39; investigation highlighted the jailing of Chasity Congious, who gave birth by herself in a cell to a baby who died after strangling on the umbilical cord.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Bloomberg Law and NBC News&#39; investigation highlighted the jailing of Chasity Congious, who gave birth by herself in a cell to a baby who died after strangling on the umbilical cord.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-11/251113-lauren-kent-carousel-4-ew-440p-adca82.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Annie Flanagan for NBC News</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Lauren Kent lost a baby to miscarriage. She now has two sons and hopes her story will help improve prenatal care in America&#39;s jails. </media:text><media:description type="plain">Lauren Kent lost a baby to miscarriage. She now has two sons and hopes her story will help improve prenatal care in America&#39;s jails. </media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260506-Sydney-Kamlager-Dove-vl-343p-cc75b4.jpg" height="1503" width="2000"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 13:00:42 GMT</pubDate><title>A new federal bill aims to protect pregnant women held in prisons and jails</title><updateDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 13:00:42 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Corky Siemaszko</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 07 May 2026 17:01:59 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Thirty former Ohio State University football players, including more than a dozen who went on to play in the NFL, signed on to the class action lawsuit brought by other ex-OSU students who say they were sexually abused decades ago by campus doctor Richard Strauss</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/dozen-former-nfl-players-join-sex-abuse-lawsuits-ohio-state-university-rcna343547</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/dozen-former-nfl-players-join-sex-abuse-lawsuits-ohio-state-university-rcna343547</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260506-ohio-state-university-stadium-ew-556p-41568b.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Stephen Zenner</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Students play soccer with the Ohio Stadium in the background</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ohio Stadium on the Ohio State University campus in 2021.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-01/260113-dr-richard-strauss-mn-1530-66bae4.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="511" width="423"><media:credit>Ohio State University</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Dr. Richard Strauss from a 1978 Ohio State University employment application.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Ohio Stadium on the Ohio State University campus in 2021.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-al-washington-ew-241p-906073.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1992" width